{{Infobox Government agency |agency_name = Central Election Commission |nativename = CIK |seal = Emblem of the CEC of Russia.svg |seal_width = 140px |formed = 1993 |headquarters = [[Moscow]] |employees = 15 |budget = |chief1_name = [[Ella Pamfilova]] |chief1_position = Chairman |website = [http://cikrf.ru/eng/ CIKRF.ru] |footnotes = }} {{Politics of Russia}} [[File:Emblem of Central Election Commission of Russia.png|150px|thumb|Emblem of the Central Election Commission]] [[File:Central Election Commission of Russia (former logo).jpg|thumb|Former logo of the Central Election Commission]]
The '''Central Election Commission of the Russian Federation''' ({{lang-ru|Центральная избирательная комиссия Российской Федерации (Центризбирком)}}) is the superior power body responsible for conducting federal [[elections]] and overseeing local elections in the [[Russian Federation]] founded in September 1993. It consists of 15 members. The [[President of Russia]], [[State Duma]] and [[Federation Council of Russia]] each appoint five members. In turn, these members elect the Chairman, Deputy Chairman and Secretary. The Commission is in power for a four-year term.
On 30 January 2007, amendments to the Russian election legislation, which would allow people without higher education in law to become members of the Central Election Commission, were passed by the [[President of Russia]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Nagornykh|first1=Irina|last2=Farizova|first2=Suzanne|last3=Khamraev|first3=Victor|title=CEC is open to experienced non-lawyers|url=http://www.kommersant.ru/doc/735390|publisher=[[Kommersant]]|accessdate=17 June 2017|language=Russian|date=20 January 2007}}</ref><ref>[http://www.rg.ru/2007/02/02/referendum-prava-dok.html]</ref>
==International Cooperation==
The CEC of Russia is a member of the [[Association of Central and Eastern European Election Officials]].<ref name=ifestudy> {{cite paper| title = Party and Campaign Funding in Eastern Europe: A Study of 18 Member Countries of the ACEEEO | author = Ikstens, Jānis and more | date = October 2001 | publisher = [[International Foundation for Electoral Systems]]}} [http://www.pervygolos.hu/conferences/2001/18-country.pdf found at Google Scholar] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20040714053424/http://www.pervygolos.hu/conferences/2001/18-country.pdf |date=2004-07-14 }}</ref>
